<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/0eeb311cea967af6ca6de7cf9e1da841.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 2 and c = 6. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>5.7</li><li>19.5</li><li>70.5</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}^{{2}}={2}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{36}={4}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{36}-{4}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{32}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{32}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5.6568542494924}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5.7}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{2}}{{6}}\right)}}}\approx{19.47122063447}\approx{19.5}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{2}}{{6}}\right)}}}\approx{70.52877936553}\approx{70.5}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

